sudo find / -name config.yaml


find . -size 2220c

b – 512-byte blocks (this is the default if no suffix is used)
c – bytes
w – two-byte words
k – Kilobytes
M – Megabytes
G – Gigabytes

by group:    find /home -group ftpusers

find directory-location -user {username} -name {file-name}

match files only:    find / -type f -user vivek -o -user wendy

match dirs only:    find / -type d -user vivek -o -user wendy

Remove errors from results for easier reading
2>/dev/null 2> file redirects stderr to file /dev/null is a blackhole of no return...

